          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/964.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span><strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>beef mince</strong> and the&nbsp;<strong>ras el hanout</strong> and cook for 3 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up as you go</p>\r\n<p>Once browned, add the <strong>sultanas</strong> and cook for a further 2 min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and set aside - this is your <strong>spiced beef</strong>&nbsp;</p>",
